Package io.honeycomb.libhoney.responses.impl

Class BatchResponseBody

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.honeycomb.libhoney.responses.impl.BatchResponseBody

  • public class BatchResponseBody
extends Object
    This class encapsulates 3 categories of responses that we might expect from the batch API.
    1. BatchResponseBody.ServerResponseCategory.BATCH_ACCEPTED, where the response code was 200 and the response body is a list of elements that provide information about success/failure of each individual event sent to the server
    2. BatchResponseBody.ServerResponseCategory.BATCH_REJECTED, where the response code was not 200 and the body contains an error message about why the batch failed.
    3. BatchResponseBody.ServerResponseCategory.CANNOT_INFER_STATE, where given the status codes conditions of 1 and 2, there was a failure to deserialize the response body.

    To be used together with LazyServerResponse to avoid the cost of repeatedly deserializing the response body.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      static int BATCH_ACCEPTED_STATUS_CODE
      The HTTP response code indicating that the batch as a whole was accepted, so we can assume that the response body is an array of response elements.
      static int BATCH_ELEMENT_SUCCESS_CODE
      The status code, found within a response element in the body, which indicates success.
